Feature Design and System Flow for School LMS Platform

A solid Learning Management System (LMS) requires structured role management (Admin, Teacher, Student) along with strict access control. During registration, users select a role (Admin/Teacher/Student) and must wait for Admin approval before gaining access. The Admin has full authority to approve, reject, or modify role requests. For example, if a user registers as an Admin but should actually be a Teacher, it is safer to reject the request and require re-registration for security reasons.

Best practices emphasize a clear role hierarchy:

Admin has full system control
Teacher manages learning content and assignments
Student accesses only relevant materials

The principle of least privilege should be applied, meaning users only receive the minimum access necessary to perform their tasks. After account creation, Admin must verify user data (such as class assignment) before activation.

