Class & User Management

Admins can:

Create classes (e.g., “Grade 10A”)
Assign students to classes
View total number of students automatically
Assign teachers with specific roles (e.g., Diniyyah, IT, Homeroom Teacher)
Promote students in bulk (Grade 10 → 11 → 12)

During registration, students must input their class. If incorrect, Admin can edit and reassign them. This gives Admin full visibility of:

Student distribution per class
Teacher assignments
Class structure and transitions
Teacher Features: Materials & Assignments

Teachers can create learning content with the following structure:

Title (e.g., “Poster Assignment” or “Diniyyah Concept Material”)
Content (file, image, or link)
Optional message/instructions
Type:
Material (view-only)
Assignment (PR) (mandatory submission)

If marked as an assignment:

A deadline must be set
Students are notified automatically

The system must visually highlight late submissions (e.g., red indicators). This allows teachers to quickly identify which students submitted late.

Teachers can also:

Review submissions
Assign grades
Provide feedback
Student Features: Access & Submission

Students can:

Access all materials anytime (24/7)
Download or view content (PDF, video, image, links)
Receive notifications for new assignments

When submitting assignments:

Input title
Upload content (file, image, or link)
Add optional message (e.g., reason for late submission)

Students can:

Track submission status (submitted / pending / late)
View grades and feedback
Attendance System (Teacher-Controlled)

Attendance is managed only by teachers to prevent dishonesty.

Teachers mark each student as:

Present (Hadir)
Excused (Izin)
Absent (Alfa)

This can be implemented using simple UI elements (buttons or dropdowns).

Admins can:

View attendance summaries per student
Filter by date range (e.g., Jan 1 – May 1)
Access statistics such as:
Total present days
Excused absences
Unexcused absences

This system ensures transparency and accountability.

